Most advanced Responsive jQuery Slider Plugin with the famous Parallax Effect and optional 3D Transitions!
responsiveUnder: You can force the slider to change automatically into responsive mode but only if the slider width is smaller than responsiveUnder pixels.
layersContainer: Creates an invisible inner container with the given dimension in pixels to hold and center your layers.
autoStart: If true, slideshow will automatically start after loading the page.
pauseOnHover: If ture, SlideShow will pause when you move the mouse pointer over the LayerSlider container.
firstSlide: LayerSlider will start with the specified slide.
animateFirstSlide: Disabling this option will result a static starting slide for the fisrt time on page load.
loops: Number of loops if autoStart set true (0 means infinite).
forceLoopNum: If true, the slider will always stop at the given number of loops even if the user restarts the slideshow.
towWaySlideshow: If true, slideshow will go backwards if you click the prev button.
randomSlideshow: If true, LayerSlider will change to a random layer instead of changing to the next / prev layer. Note that 'loops' feature won't work with randomSlideshow!
globalBGColor: Background color of LayerSlider. You can use all CSS methods, like hexa colors, rgb(r,g,b) method, color names, etc. Note, that background sublayers are covering the background.
globalBGImage: Background image of LayerSlider. This will be a fixed background image of LayerSlider by default. Note, that background sublayers are covering the global background image.
navPrevNext: If false, Prev and Next buttons will be invisible.
navStartStop: If false, Start and Stop buttons will be invisible.
navButtons: If false, slide buttons will be invisible.
hoverPrevNext: If true, the prev and next buttons will be shown only if you move your mouse over the slider.
hoverBottomNav: If true, the bottom navigation controls (with also thumbnails) will be shown only if you move your mouse over the slider.
keybNav: Keyboard navigation. You can navigate with the left and right arrow keys.
showBarTimer: You can show or hide the bar timer.
showCircleTimer: You can show or hide the circle timer.
thumbnailNavigation: Thumbnail navigation mode. Note, that 'hover' setting needs navButtons true!
tnContainerWidth: Default width of the thumbnail container.
tnActiveOpacity: Opacity of the active thumbnail.
tnInactiveOpacity: Opacity of the Inactive thumbnail.
autoPlayVideos: If true, slider will autoplay youtube / vimeo videos - you can use it with autoPauseSlideshow.

autoPauseSlideshow: 'auto', true or false. 'auto' means, if autoPlayVideos is set to true, slideshow will stop UNTIL the video is playing and after that it continues. True means slideshow will stop and it won't continue after video is played.
youtubePreview: Default thumbnail picture of YouTube videos.
imgPreload: Preloads all images and background-images of the next layer.
lazyLoad: Loads images only when needed to save bandwidth and server resouces. Relies on the preload feature.
yourLogo: A fixed image layer can be shown above the slider that remains still during slide progression. Can be used to display logos or watermarks.
yourLogoStyle: CSS properties to control the image placement and appearance.
yourLogoLink: Enter an URL to link the YourLogo image.
